$interpreted: Tindoiimu: I understand—your master has sent you here to let me know she's ok. Thank you for the message. Go back, now.
Tindoiimu: It's still light outside—no one will see your glow, so you won't be caught. Tell your master to take care of herself.
Restless Soldier: That letter... what should we do? It won't cause any trouble, will it?
Serious Soldier: Well, you know what they say. What can go wrong, will...
Tindoiimu: ...Did something happen?
Serious Soldier: The insect princess? What do you want?
Tindoiimu: I'm here to sign up for the Martial Arts Tournament. Here's my tali—
Restless Soldier: Sign-up's been delayed! Come back in a few days!
Tindoiimu: ...Delayed? Why?
Restless Soldier: How should I know? It's just delayed, alright? Come back later!
Serious Soldier: Let's lock the door. We don't need anybody else comin' around and botherin' us!
Seahorse Contestant: Well, isn't this the mighty Insect Tribe princess?
Tindoiimu: Peaches on your head... you all must be the Bull, Wolf, and Seahorse contestants.
Seahorse Contestant: Hmph, even insects know, huh? That's right, these peaches represent a pact between us that transcends tribal—
Tindoiimu: So you all couldn't sign up either, right? Do you know why there's been a delay?
Seahorse Contestant: Did she just... interrupt me?
Wolf Contestant: Well damn, you really want to sign up? Be careful what you wish for.
Bull Contestant: You know, maybe it's for the best you ran into us here.
Bull Contestant: Some maggot says she'll cut down the Udumbara, and thinks she can get away with it?
Bull Contestant: Don't let your guard down! It's just one of her, and three of us! This should be easy!
Bull Contestant: Let's show her the power of the peach!

Juan Yun: So you do realize it's a completely unfair fight? 
...Might as well just eat those stupid peaches, before they rot.
Seahorse Contestant: Oh, it's just that talisman-snatching little waste-of-space qilin.

Wolf Contestant: Must be nice not having to compete~ 
Now you've got free time to poke your nose in other people's business.
Himawari: What did you say!?
Juan Yun: Why don't we even the odds? Add Himawari and me, that's three against three.
Tindoiimu: I don't need any help from the Alliance!
Himawari: And I never agreed to fight for her, either!
Wolf Contestant: Haha, well that was quick. Still looking for a beating, qilin lord? We won't go easy on you.
Himawari: Hey, I said I wouldn't fight for the bug—but if you wanna hurt Juan Yun, then you've got another thing coming!
Seahorse Contestant: You think we're scared? Us three grew up in the Alliance, training our whole lives. We're not scared of some little leopard orphan!
Bull Contestant: You know what, forget it. We're adults, here. Why are we wasting our time with some cripple and two chicks?
Wolf Contestant: Wait, what?
Seahorse Contestant: Why the sudden—
Bull Contestant: I said let's drop it! The Alliance sees what's going on here and we're toast. Go go go...
Bull Contestant: They were too worked up, I couldn't hold 'em! No hard feelings, alright?
Himawari: Hmph.
Juan Yun: Did they hurt you?
Tindoiimu: No.
Himawari: Juan Yun cares about you. Why don't you show some respect?
Tindoiimu: I didn't ask for his help.
Juan Yun: Himawari, why don't you go back. We've got some things to talk about.
Himawari: I... no! You said you'd spend the day with me!
Juan Yun: Himawari, do as I say.
Himawari: ...Then you'll come see me later?
Juan Yun: Of course, it'll just be me and you for the next few days. Just give me a moment here.
Himawari: Fine... You better not try anything funny with my big brother.
